The paper discusses the use of deep neural networks for decision tree models, which is a topic related to machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves the use of neural networks, which falls under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also deals with tabular data, which is a topic related to data science and data analysis, and hence cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is another likely sub-category. Furthermore, the paper evaluates the efficacy of the proposed model on several datasets, which is a topic related to computer vision and image processing, and hence cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper investigates the similarities and differences between DNDT and vanilla decision trees, which is a topic related to artificial intelligence and machine learning, and hence cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible sub-category.
